To make your website accessible from any search engine:
Choose a Hosting Service: You can choose from platforms like Heroku, DigitalOcean, Google Cloud, or AWS.
Deploy the Application:
Heroku:
Create an account on Heroku.
Install the Heroku CLI.
Use the CLI to create a new app and push your code to it.
DigitalOcean:
Create a Droplet (a virtual server) and set up your Flask application on it.
Domain Name: Purchase a domain name or use the one provided by your hosting service to make it accessible via the internet.
